### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

core

### Is this a regression?

No

### Description

The following template throws NG0300: 
```
@defer(on immediate) { 
   @for (item of items; track item.id) {
     <item [id]="item.id" />
    } 
} 
@for (item of items; track item.id) {
 <item [id]="item.id" />
} 
```

Here we have a template where the same dependency is located inside and outside the `@defer`. 

Note: It might be fixed by #51964, but not sure.  

[Demo](https://stackblitz.com/edit/angular-at-qguzbb?file=src%2Fmain.ts)

### Please provide the environment you discovered this bug in (run `ng version`)

```true
v17.0.0-next.6
```

### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

core

### Is this a regression?

No

### Description

Defer block won't chunk the components that are used with a forwardRef. 

```ts
@Component({
  selector: 'app-root',
  standalone: true,
  imports: [forwardRef(() => DeferMeCmp)],
  template: `
    <button (click)="show.set(!show())">show</button>
    <div>
      @if (show()) { 
         @defer (on immediate) {
           <defer-me />
         }
      }
    </div>
  `,
})
export class AppComponent {
  show = signal(false);
}


// defer-me.cmp.ts

@Component({
  selector: 'defer-me',
  template: ` <div>Defered!</div> `,
  standalone: true,
})
export class DeferMeCmp {}
```

