### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

router

### Is this a regression?

Yes

### Description

When migrating to angular 16, navigating to any page in my application was basically not working anymore. Page would just route back to the beginning of the app. After testing a few things, I found out this was the issue:
```
@Injectable({
  providedIn: 'root'
})
export class Guard  {
  canActivate(route: ActivatedRouteSnapshot) {
    const url = route.url.pop().path;
  }
}
```

After changing `route.url.pop()` to `route.url.slice().pop()`, the problem went away. Seems that since angular 16, the `url` is not immutable anymore? and just using `pop` will basically make the whole routing go haywire?

